  <h1 style="bottom: -10px; position: relative;">Certification Program</h1>
  <hr>
  <p>Certification program gives owners and their bots a certified status and more exposure for their creation, bots are expected to be well maintained and online 24/7.</p>
  <h2>Requirements:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Server Count must be higher than 250.</li>
    <li>Must have at least 30 votes at the time of submission.</li>
    <li>A good use of short and long description.</li>
    <li>Must post server count to our API.</li>
    <li>Online 24/7, excepting some minor downtime or maintenances.</li>
    <li>Original code, not a fork of a bot with a new name.</li>
    <li>Be on list for at least 3 days.</li>
    <li>Full documentation of your commands and features.</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>Perks:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>A role for you and your bot.</li>
    <li>Huge chances on appearing on first page.</li>
    <li>Access to exclusive text and voice channels.</li>
    <li>Vanity URLs.</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>Reviewing System:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Discord Bot Best Practices (<a style="color: #7289da;" href="https://github.com/meew0/discord-bot-best-practices">More about them here.</a>)</li>
    <li>Functionality</li>
    <li>Concept</li>
    <li>Creativity</li>
    <li>Description Use</li>
    <li>Support Quality</li>
    <li>Past Reports</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We will allocate points for all of the areas listed below, if your bot scores over a certain threshold, your bot and you will be certified.</p>
  <p><strong>IMPORTANT NOTE:</strong> We are <!--strong>not</strong--> looking for <strong>any type of bots</strong> and/or main purpose of the bot is 8ball or any other random number generated command and we also don't look for <strong>non-english speaking bots</strong>, if your bot supports multiple languages, make sure the default is <strong>english</strong>.</p>
<p>
  If you feel that you meet these criteria, why don't you apply <a style="color: #7289da;" href="/certification/apply">here?</a> 
  </p>
